title.narrative: TORP 18-060 (OES EQT Positions (1)). This Order Procures Professional Support Services To Assist Environmental Quality And Transboundary Issues (Oes/E/Eqt) Office With Fulfilling Their Mission.

description.narrative: ADMINISTRATIVE MANAGEMENT [Covers individual experts and consultants possessing special, current knowledge, and skill which may be combined with extensive operational experience. They provide information, opinions, advice, or recommendations that enhance understanding of complex issues or improve the quality and timeliness of policy development and decision-making. Contract experts and consultants do not supervise or perform operating functions nor do they receive direct supervision. Contract experts and consultants serving on advisory committees are to be assigned to subobject code 2505.]. This modification hereby: 1. Exercise Option Year 2 (09/28/2020 to 9/27/2021) 2. Fully funds option year 2 line item 2001 (labor) to allow for continued support services. 3. Fully funds option year 2 line item 2002 (travel) to allow for government approved travel..
